div.div: If trices as bare are inside bytes source there are max 1-3 bytes to ignore (case Discarder). If trices are wrapped 'ignored' can contain any number of bytes and these are some different encodings. One encoding is 'dynamic strings' (handled inside TriceInterpreterWithDynamicStrings) and others encodings can be some commands ( case CmdHandler)

div.div: The TriceReceivers use an io.Reader for reception and provide an interface for getting 2 output channels. One for the trices and one for the ignored bytes. The 2 channels give sync information where ignored bytes are located between trices.

div.div:
The TriceInterpreters generate log lines from the trices and use the trice ID list til.json as look-up table for the received trice IDs. The TriceInterpreterWithDynamicStrings
filters the next dynamic string from the ignored bytes on reception of an appropriate trigger trice.
